Giro Velogames Daily Update

Race Results - Stage 20




Heres the non-spoiler 5min highlight clip on Youtube:

https://youtu.be/hDzCWYsX_zM





A select group of GC contenders made the expected break on the final climb of last nights Stage 20 battle. Thibaut Pinot claimed his first Giro victory, taking the sprint ahead of Ilnur Zakarin and Nibali. Although Tom Dumoulin trailed this group and Pinot replaced the Dutchman in third position overall, Dumoulin sits only 53 seconds behind race leader Quintana. Not enough of a buffer for any of the riders holding the top three spots is the opinion of most top cycling analysts with Big Tom expected to gain at least as much as this in tonights final stage Individual Time Trial.
